</i><br>
<br>
This type of thing verant strayed away from as far as i could tell because it would become 'the only way' to kill a mob.<br>
<br>
Look games like AC (yeah i know you hate the game, but every other rpg has a similar system) where there is a bit more differentiation in combat.  Each mob has a different set of resistances and weaknesses.  If i am fighting say a wood golem, i use a fire sword.  Against a rock golem, i use a bludgeoning weapon if i have one.  It is totally possible to work out a system for each mob to make the battle easy.<br>
<br>
In EQ its as you said, you don't have these options, you either can root and nuke, kite, or tank it with healer support.  Magic is the only real way to make any shortcuts.<br>
<br>
Also a game where real combat is implemented, timing and combinations of attacks are the key.  These are almost impossible over the internet due to lag and each players varying computer speeds.<br>
<br>
Also EQ is pretty much based around requiring a group to kill anything worthwhile.  How do you simulate 20 people all hacking at the neck of the dragon, while 10 people hack at its stomach, while at the same time measuring the seperate effects being real time generated by people with various latencies and system speeds?  Not very possible.  <br>
<br>
